description.narrative: In 2019, 663 community health workers and 365 health staff had their knowledge increased and skills enhanced to provide quality care of children with acute malnutrition and screened 186,338 children under five for malnutrition, referred and treated, 19,143 children with moderate acute malnutrition and 6,267 children with severe acute malnutrition in 28 inpatient facilities and 210 outpatient treatment programme sites in 23 municipalities of Cunene, Huila, Bié, and Namibe provinces. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
